trans-unit.source: Azure API Management REST API Group entity
trans-unit.target: Azure API Management REST API Group entity

trans-unit.source: Groups are used to manage the visibility of products to developers.
trans-unit.target: Groups are used to manage the visibility of products to developers.

trans-unit.source: Each <token>azure_apimgt_3</token> service instance comes with the following immutable system groups whose membership is automatically managed by <token>azure_apimgt_3</token>.
trans-unit.target: Each <token>azure_apimgt_3</token> service instance comes with the following immutable system groups whose membership is automatically managed by <token>azure_apimgt_3</token>.

trans-unit.source: <legacyBold>Administrators</legacyBold> - Azure subscription administrators are members of this group.
trans-unit.target: <legacyBold>Administrators</legacyBold> - Azure subscription administrators are members of this group.

trans-unit.source: <legacyBold>Developers</legacyBold> - Authenticated developer portal users fall into this group.
trans-unit.target: <legacyBold>Developers</legacyBold> - Authenticated developer portal users fall into this group.

trans-unit.source: <legacyBold>Guests</legacyBold> - Unauthenticated developer portal users are placed into this group.
trans-unit.target: <legacyBold>Guests</legacyBold> - Unauthenticated developer portal users are placed into this group.

trans-unit.source: In addition to these system groups, administrators can create custom groups or <externalLink><linkText>leverage external groups in associated Azure Active Directory tenants</linkText><linkUri>https://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/articles/api-management-howto-aad/#how-to-add-an-external-azure-active-directory-group</linkUri></externalLink>.
trans-unit.target: In addition to these system groups, administrators can create custom groups or <externalLink><linkText>leverage external groups in associated Azure Active Directory tenants</linkText><linkUri>https://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/articles/api-management-howto-aad/#how-to-add-an-external-azure-active-directory-group</linkUri></externalLink>.

trans-unit.source: Custom and external groups can be used alongside system groups in giving developers visibility and access to API products.
trans-unit.target: Custom and external groups can be used alongside system groups in giving developers visibility and access to API products.

trans-unit.source: For example, you could create one custom group for developers affiliated with a specific partner organization and allow them access to the APIs from a product containing relevant APIs only.
trans-unit.target: For example, you could create one custom group for developers affiliated with a specific partner organization and allow them access to the APIs from a product containing relevant APIs only.

trans-unit.source: A user can be a member of more than one group.
trans-unit.target: A user can be a member of more than one group.

trans-unit.source: This topic describes how to manage groups using the <token>azure_apimgt_3</token> REST API.
trans-unit.target: This topic describes how to manage groups using the <token>azure_apimgt_3</token> REST API.

trans-unit.source: This operation removes the specified user from the specified group.
trans-unit.target: This operation removes the specified user from the specified group.

trans-unit.target: This operation has the following responses.

trans-unit.source: The user was successfully removed from the group.
